Sentencas: In the development of nanoscale oxygen electrodes of high-temperature solid oxide cells (SOCs), the interface formed between the nanoelectrode particles and the electrolyte or electrolyte scaffolds is the most critical.
Titulo: Development of Nanostructured Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite/Gadolinian-Doped Ceria Composite Electrodes of Solid Oxide Cells Formed by In Situ Polarization

Sentencas: In this work, a new synthesis technique for the fabrication of nanostructured electrodes via in situ electrochemical polarization treatment is reported.
Titulo: Development of Nanostructured Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite/Gadolinian-Doped Ceria Composite Electrodes of Solid Oxide Cells Formed by In Situ Polarization

Sentencas: The lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite (LSCF) precursor solution is infiltrated into a gadolinia-doped ceria (GDC) scaffold presintered on a yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte, followed by in situ polarization current treatment at SOC operation temperatures.
Titulo: Development of Nanostructured Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite/Gadolinian-Doped Ceria Composite Electrodes of Solid Oxide Cells Formed by In Situ Polarization

Sentencas: Electrode ohmic and polarization resistances decrease with an increase in the polarization current treatment.
Titulo: Development of Nanostructured Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite/Gadolinian-Doped Ceria Composite Electrodes of Solid Oxide Cells Formed by In Situ Polarization

Sentencas: Detailed microstructure analysis indicates the formation of a convex-shaped interface between the LSCF nanoparticles (NPs) and the GDC scaffold, very different from the flat contact between LSCF and GDC observed after heating at 800 degrees C with no polarization current treatment.
Titulo: Development of Nanostructured Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite/Gadolinian-Doped Ceria Composite Electrodes of Solid Oxide Cells Formed by In Situ Polarization

Sentencas: The embedded LSCF NPs on the GDC scaffold contribute to the superior stability under both fuel cell and electrolysis operation conditions at 750 degrees C and a high peak power density of 1.58 W cm(-2) at 750 degrees C.
Titulo: Development of Nanostructured Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite/Gadolinian-Doped Ceria Composite Electrodes of Solid Oxide Cells Formed by In Situ Polarization

Sentencas: This work highlights a novel and facile route to in situ construct a stable and high-performing nanostructured electrode for SOCs.
Titulo: Development of Nanostructured Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite/Gadolinian-Doped Ceria Composite Electrodes of Solid Oxide Cells Formed by In Situ Polarization
